In order to determine the orientation, we need to calculate the Eular angles (Roll, Pitch, Yaw) which provide a more intuitive representation of the attitude of the IMUs. We already have the quaterions obtained from `immu_orientaiton`, so now let's convert those quaternians to Eular Angles.
This will help us understand the orientation in terms of Roll (rotation around X-axis), Pitch (rotation along Y-axis) and Yaw (rotation about Z-axis).

